==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Panorama
<hw>Pan`o*ra"ma</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr.
<grk>pa^s</grk>, <grk>pa^n</grk>, all + <?/ that which is seen, a view,
fr. <?/ to see. See <er>Pan-</er>, and <er>Wary</er>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>A complete view in every direction.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <specif>Hence:</specif> <def>A comprehensive survey of a
particular topic; also, a broad view of the development of a series of
events.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>A picture presenting a view of objects in every
direction, as from a central point.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>A picture representing scenes too extended to be
beheld at once, and so exhibited a part at a time, by being unrolled,
and made to pass continuously before the spectator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Panoramical</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Panoramic</ent>⟦br⟧
